headline: Stocks hold steady on Wall Street as earnings roll in
summary: Stocks on Wall Street were down slightly in early trading Thursday, following new economic data and a mixed batch of earnings reports from big U.S. companies.  Hormel fell 4.7% for the biggest drop among S&P 500 companies after reporting earnings that Spam maker fell short of Wall Street’s forecasts and cut its outlook for the year.  Tech giant Nvidia was down 1% a day after reporting quarterly earnings and revenue that beat Wall Street analysts’ forecasts, though the company noted that sales of its artificial intelligence chipsets rose at a slower pace than analysts anticipated.
